The team used resting-state fMRI brain scans (where kids lie still while
the scanner records brain activity) and compared them with dozens of
personal and family traits. They looked for patterns using a method
called *Canonical
Correlation Analysis*, which can find hidden connections between two big
sets of data=E2=80=94in this case, brain wiring and behavior/lifestyle.

